        "heading": "Clinical Note",
        "section_value": "Chief Complaint\nReports headaches and elevated blood pressure.\nHistory of Present Illness\nThe patient reports a history of high blood pressure for an extended period, previously prescribed chlorthalidone which he discontinued due to stomach discomfort. He experiences headaches, often described as throbbing, located on the top of his head, and reports occasional dizziness and blurred vision associated with these headaches. He occasionally takes Tylenol for headache relief. He has been experiencing these symptoms for an extended period.\nFindings\nPhysical examination revealed blood pressure readings consistently above 170/98, with bilateral pitting edema noted on the upper extremities and lower extremities (1+). Heart rate was within normal limits, and oxygen saturation was adequate. Lung auscultation revealed a grade 2 systolic ejection murmur, which was present last year. No jugular venous distention or carotid bruits were detected.\nAssessment\nThe patient presents with uncontrolled hypertension and associated edema.\nPlan",
